00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:43,360
and then into this, crossing over.

85
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,160
The crossing over takes there,

86
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:51,120
but the root of the Ego and Super-Ego starts at this point.

87
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:59,240
Shri Krishna, as we know, appeared to Arjuna

88
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:05,160
as a Virata, as the Great Primordial Being.

89
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:11,840
He saw Him as a very huge, big personality.

90
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,360
And he saw in Him

91
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:17,800
all the human beings and all the creations moving about.

92
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,640
And he couldn't bear it anymore, he said,

93
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:22,360
"I don't want to see it again."

94
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:26,280
Shri Krishna told the Gita,

95
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:31,120
spoke the Gita only to Arjuna, only to one person.

96
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:34,720
He didn't tell it to even the second person,

97
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:37,720
because He was born 6,000 years back.

98
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:40,640
That time the maturity of people was so low,

99
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:47,320
that He did not tell about this to anybody else but Arjuna.

100
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:52,720
And this was heard by another person, who wrote it down

101
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:56,000
and Vyasa is the poet, who wrote about it.

102
00:07:56,200 --> 00:08:01,520
The Gita is the Vedanta - means the end of Vedas.

103
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,440
Vedas have got two sides.

104
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:06,360
The first side is where the mantras are there

105
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:10,760
to excite the right side or we can say the elements

106
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:14,080
and the end of it is the philosophy.

107
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:19,080
And He used that philosophy of Gita.

108
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:23,040
He used that Vedanta philosophy in Gita

109
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:26,800
to explain what is knowledge,

110
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:30,600
what is God, what is Spirit,

111
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:34,680
how to achieve it, and what happens.

112
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:39,520
Now, Krishna's basic character of

113
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,480
His advent, was that.

114
00:08:43,680 --> 00:08:45,480
So far for Rama,

115
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:48,120
He was the one who lived like a human being,

116
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:52,240
and established a

117
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,960
special place

118
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:59,000
or say established a special character

119
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:02,640
of a benevolent king, for other kings to follow.

120
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,960
But this one, when He came

121
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:09,480
He found that the whole place was filled with ritualism,

122
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:12,960
with all kinds of dead

123
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:16,400
supraconscious activities and subconscious activities,

124
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:19,600
and people were indulging into

125
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:23,200
materialistic things and were very unhappy.

126
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:27,360
So, He established Himself

127
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:32,200
as the incarnation of the play - leela.

128
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:35,400
That the whole world is just a drama.

129
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:39,040
It's just a drama and you are a witness to it.

130
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:42,200
Actually what happens when you watch a drama,

131
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:46,200
you feel that you are in it.

132
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:48,520
Supposing there is Napoleon

133
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,200
or somebody who is in the drama.

134
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:53,840
You start feeling you are Napoleon and even when you go home,

135
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,840
you talk like Napoleon for a while.

136
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,960
You carry on the joke with you.

137
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:02,440
But it's a drama, it's outside you. It is not you.

138
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:06,840
Sometimes when there is, say, a cinema or something we see,

139
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:11,560
we identify ourselves with the scene so much that we cry,

140
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:14,880
weep, sometimes feeling very excited.

141
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:17,440
But when the drama is over

142
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:21,160
then we'll suddenly realize, "Oh God, it was a drama."

143
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:27,320
In the same way this whole life, human life is a drama.

144
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:30,320
And the whole drama

145
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:34,640
is only seen when you get your Realization, you become a witness.

146
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:37,600
Now those who have got Realization,

147
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:41,040
should understand that you have become now a witness.

148
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:43,880
Start seeing everything and you'll be amazed,

149
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:47,680
you'll feel "Oh, I'm so much away, I'm just witnessing."

150
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:51,040
There's a Sahaja yogini who came from India

151
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:53,400
and she had never travelled before anywhere,

152
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,400
even by plane she had never travelled before.

153
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:58,040
And comes from a very traditional family,

154
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:01,160
she has never been out without somebody going with her.

155
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,400
Such a person.

156
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:05,600
She got her Realization and she came to America.

157
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:08,600
She told me that I never felt that I was going to America,

158
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,520
that I was going by plane anywhere,

159
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:13,200
that I should be frightened. Nothing of the kind.

160
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,960
And they were all telling me be careful,

161
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:17,200
I was wondering what are they worried about.

162
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:20,760
I was least bothered, the whole thing looked like a drama,

163
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,960
I got into the plane, I came here

164
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:26,760
and there was a sea of human beings, I couldn't see my brother,

165
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,400
and I think I got lost.

166
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,600
I said, "Alright, if I'm lost doesn't matter.

167
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,080
I'm never lost because I'm with myself."

168
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:35,040
So I was going to the taxi fellow,

169
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:37,960
I was going to tell him,"Take me down to my brother's place,"

170
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:42,840
then suddenly the brother got her, got to her and found her.

171
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:45,280
But otherwise she was saying "I was so relaxed,

172
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:46,480
I was least bothered,

173
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:49,160
most surprising I was witnessing the whole drama,

174
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:54,200
without any, without any consideration about it

175
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:58,200
or any awareness about it, I was just doing it automatically."

176
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:00,160
That's what happens to you.

177
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:05,040
You see the death, and you see the life, and you see the drama.

178
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:08,160
And you do not get involved with it.

179
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:10,280
When you are not involved into it,

180
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:14,800
then you are completely at ease and at peace.

181
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:19,160
As I gave you the example, that if you are in the water,

182
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,480
then you are worried about the waves.

183
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:24,360
But supposing you get into the boat,

184
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:28,200
then you see the waves as fun.

185
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:32,640
Or if you know how to swim, also you can see it as a fun.

186
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:36,400
So when you get realized, when you get your realization,

187
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:39,240
then the whole thing becomes like a drama

188
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:43,320
and you start developing your detachment.

189
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,520
So He's the Yogeshwara.

190
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:51,480
He's the one, who is fully, detachment. He's a full detachment.

191
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,400
Though He was a king.

192
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:57,400
Though He was having a very luxurious life,

193
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:00,000
He was a detached personality.

194
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:03,840
Now He, on this earth, when He came,

195
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,960
He had to have His powers with Him.

196
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:10,440
And He didn't know, how to bring those powers in human beings,

197
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:13,600
because He knew, He wouldn't be able to give Realization to people

198
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:16,080
at that time 6,000 years back.

199
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:22,400
So, He created a method by which He got 16,000 wives.

200
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:26,880
And all these wives were nothing but His powers carrying people.

201
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:29,800
And there's a big story about it, which

202
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:35,280
I think every Indian knows and you can also find out.

203
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:39,360
He had five, I mean He became the king, He did all this,

204
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:43,600
and He had five elements as His wives.

205
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:48,240
So His own queens, five of them, were five elements

206
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:53,760
and 16,000 wives were actually His own powers

207
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,880
manifested as human beings.

208
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:59,120
And He came on this earth as Krishna.

209
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:04,120
"Krishi" - Krishi means agriculture, means actually sowing.

210
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:09,400
He sowed the seed, He sowed the seed of spirituality.

211
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:14,400
He said, "Nainam Chindanti Shastrani,

212
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:16,200
nainam Dahati Pavakah,

213
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,400
na Chainam Kledayanty apo,

214
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,400
na Shosayati Marutah."

215
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:26,000
Means this Spirit cannot be killed, it cannot be sucked in,

216
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,000
it cannot be destroyed,

217
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:33,080
neither it can be transformed - it's eternal.

218
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:37,360
And to prove that, Christ came on this earth at this point,

219
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:41,880
and He by His resurrection proved it that it cannot be killed.

220
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:47,200
Now I will tell you about Shri Krishna's life as a diplomat.

221
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,000
He was a diplomat.

222
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:53,080
He was an incarnation of diplomacy.

223
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,800
And the best diplomacy is such,

224
00:14:57,080 --> 00:15:01,360
that you give such conditions which are absurd.

225
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:04,000
If you give absurd conditions,

226
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:06,920
then a person gets toppled down over it,

227
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:08,920
and then he succumbs.

228
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:12,320
Because if you approach directly someone

229
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:14,520
then the people are very half-baked,

230
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:18,240
and they start intellectualizing everything and rationalizing.

231
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:21,200
So better thing is put a proposition before them

232
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:24,760
which is absurd, and let them find out for themselves

233
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:29,720
and then they come to you with surrendered mind.

234
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:32,240
Now I'll explain to you how.

235
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:34,800
Arjuna was His disciple,

236
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,680
and Arjuna when he went to war

237
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:42,480
with Kauravas, who were the Satanic forces in those days,

238
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:46,280
got into a mood of despondence and he said that,

239
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,720
"These are... in these are my relations,

240
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:50,680
these are... there's my, one of my Gurus,

241
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:53,400
who taught me how to use the arrow

242
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:56,520
and how am I to fight these people?"

243
00:15:56,920 --> 00:16:01,880
So then He told the Gita, that time He spoke the Gita to him.

244
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:06,720
And He said that - the first thing He said,

245
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:11,000
that you should find your Self. You must have self-knowledge.

246
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,680
You should get realization.

247
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:15,600
You should have the knowledge.

248
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:19,760
Knowledge doesn't mean the idea about this architecture and all,

249
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:24,960
but knowledge is the awareness of your Spirit.

250
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,760
So Arjuna being a,

251
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:29,800
that time a mediocre I should say, an intellectual,

252
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,080
He asked Him a question,

253
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:33,280
as usual intellectuals are good at asking questions -

254
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:35,760
never giving answers.

255
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,840
So the intellectual asked Him,

256
